FBIS4-63464 "drsov099_e_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Kravchuk, U.S. Financier Discuss Further Aid Kravchuk, U.S. Financier Discuss Further Aid LD2005183194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1600 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005183194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] Today, Ukraine's President Leonid Kravchuk received George Soros, a well-known financier, [word indistinct] and U.S. public figure. There was a conversation, a significant part of which was held in the absence of press representatives. Various aspects of further aid to Ukraine on the part of the Soros Foundation were discussed during the conversation. Leonid Kravchuk emphasized that in our state they highly assess the humanistic activity of this foundation and are grateful for the aid that is so necessary today for the Ukrainian state. After the conversation George Soros granted an interview to journalists in which he, in particular, emphasized that during his meeting with the president, apart from stating positive factors of cooperation with our state, they also discussed an issue on exempting from taxation separate kinds of aid extended by the Soros Foundation to Ukraine. This will significantly expand the possibilities of its activities in Ukraine.
